text.section:
This subtitle does not affect a person's right to:
manufacture, sell, or offer to sell a rifle or other weapon that is not defined as a handgun in § 4-201 of the Criminal Law Article;
manufacture a prototype handgun model required for design, development, testing, and approval by the Board; and
manufacture in this State a handgun that is not on the handgun roster by a federally licensed gun manufacturer who is also licensed as a regulated firearms dealer in this State for direct sale to a unit of:
the federal government;
a state other than this State;
a local government in a state other than this State; or
a law enforcement agency in a state other than this State.
